HEADWORD: natica
<hw>nat"i*ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>naticas</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, L. <plw>naticae</plw>
<pr>(-s⟦emac⟧)</pr>.</plu> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous
species of marine gastropods belonging to <gen>Natica</gen>,
<gen>Lunatia</gen>, <gen>Neverita</gen>, and other allied genera (family
<fam>Naticidae</fam>.) They burrow beneath the sand, or mud, and drill
other shells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

